results.deck: Sony Computer Entertainment Incorporated is a subsidiary of the Sony Corporation responsible for Research & Development, production, and sales of hardware and software for the PlayStation line of handheld and video game consoles.
results.description:
Internal First-Party Developers

Sony Computer Entertainment Japan

  • Polyphony Digital - Gran Turismo series, Tourist Trophy
  • SCE Japan Studio - LocoRoco series, Ape Escape series, Patapon series, Siren series
  • Team ICO - ICO, Shadow Of The Colossus

Sony Computer Entertainment America

  • Incognito Entertainment (defunct) - Twisted Metal series, Warhawk, Downhill Domination
  • Naughty Dog - Crash Bandicoot series, Jak & Daxter series, Uncharted series
  • Bend Studio - Syphon Filter series, Resistance: Retribution
  • SCE San Diego Studio - MLB: The Show series, NBA series, The Mark Of Kri
  • SCE Santa Monica Studio - God Of War series, Warhawk
  • Sony Online Entertainment - DC Universe Online, EverQuest series, PlanetSide, Star Wars Galaxies
  • Zipper Interactive - SOCOM: US Navy SEALs series, M.A.G.: Massive Action Game, Crimson Skies (closed in March 2012)
  • Sucker Punch Productions - Sly Cooper series, inFamous

Sony Computer Entertainment Europe

All SCEE studios are based in England with the exception of Guerrilla Games, which is based in Holland.

  • Bigbig Studios - Pursuit Force (closed Jan 2012)
  • Evolution Studios - MotorStorm series, World Rally Championship series
  • Guerrilla Games - Killzone series
  • SCE London Studio - SingStar series, EyeToy series, EyePet
  • SCE Studio Cambridge - MediEvil series, PlayTV
  • SCE Studio Liverpool - WipEout series (closed in August 2012)
  • Media Molecule - LittleBigPlanet series

Second-Party Developers

  • Clap Hanz - Hot Shots series
  • Insomniac Games - Spyro series, Ratchet & Clank series, Resistance series
  • Relentless Software - Buzz! series

Corporate Leaders

Current

  • Kazuo Hirai - President and Group CEO, SCEI
  • Shuhei Yoshida - President, SCE Worldwide Studios
  • Jack Tretton - President and CEO, SCEA
  • David Reeves - President and CEO, SCEE

Former

  • Ken Kutaragi - Chairman and CEO, SCEI (1993-2006)
